### TypeScript Usage with Google APIs Client

Source: https://googleapis.dev/nodejs/googleapis/latest/index

Illustrates how to use the Google API client library with TypeScript, including importing namespaces for services and types, initializing clients, and defining request parameters with generated types. It highlights type inference and explicit type declarations.

```typescript
import {
  google,   // The top level object used to access services
  drive_v3, // For every service client, there is an exported namespace
  Auth,     // Namespace for auth related types
  Common,   // General types used throughout the library
} from 'googleapis';

// Note: using explicit types like `Auth.GoogleAuth` are only here for
// demonstration purposes.  Generally with TypeScript, these types would
// be inferred.
const auth: Auth.GoogleAuth = new google.auth.GoogleAuth();
const drive: drive_v3.Drive = google.drive({
  version: 'v3',
  auth,
});

